 same if you keep changing your sadhana and deity every few years or m=\r\nonths. After success is attain in ONE sadhana, one is free to move to any o=\r\nther. But at one point, one should ideally stick to one for the simple reas=\r\non that success with the worship of even one deity is so difficult. It does=\r\n not come in one day and in fact it may ofen take many lifetimes for ordina=\r\nry souls like us. Therefore, it is the most practical=C2=A0 strategy to foc=\r\nus on one at a time rather than many simultaneously and in the process achi=\r\neve nothing. \n=C2=A0\nSri Aadi Shankaracharya probably attained self-realiza=\r\ntion through the single marg=C2=A0of gyana/meditation and then went on to c=\r\nompose various hymns to other aspects of teh divine. Same maybe the case wi=\r\nth Sri Muththuswamy Dikshitar. You see even Ramakrishna had visions and exp=\r\neriences of so many deities from Krishna to Shiva to Jesus and Kaali. But h=\r\nis first communion was with Kaali. \n=C2=A0\nIf you achieve success in the sa=\r\ndhana of one deity and then want to experience other deities, that maybe qu=\r\nite possible. But to reach a stage of realization, one should ideally stick=\r\n to one path/one sadhana one deity.\n=C2=A0\nI hope I could explain what I am=\r\n trying to get at.\n=C2=A0\n-Regards\n=C2=A0Rajarshi\n=C2=A0\n\n\n=C2=A0\n\n&quot;Between=\r\n me and You, there is only me.\nTake away the me, so only You remain&quot; - Hall=\r\naj\n\n--- On Thu, 4/3/10, Nagraj Kota &lt;nagraj_um@...&gt; wrote:\n\n\nFrom: Na=\r\ngraj Kota &lt;nagraj_um@...&gt;\nSubject: Re: [vedic-wisdom] Surrender (Re: =\r\nAghora books..)\nTo: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com\nDate: Thursday, 4 March, 2=\r\n010, 1:18 AM\n\n\n=C2=A0 \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nDear Sri Utpalji and Rajarshiji, \n=C2=A0\nT=\r\nhank you for the response. I do understand that Telang Swamy might have bee=\r\nn a great yogi but my point is how are we to understand that greatness and =\r\nin that context what is ununsual in